n",{"type":1407,"content":9179},[9180],{"type":112,"attrs":9181,"content":9182},{"textAlign":139},[9183],{"text":9184,"type":75},"Camera lens cleaning and positioning adjustments",{"type":1407,"content":9186},[9187],{"type":112,"attrs":9188,"content":9189},{"textAlign":139},[9190],{"text":9191,"type":75},"Network connectivity tests to ensure seamless data transmission",{"type":112,"attrs":9193,"content":9194},{"textAlign":6932},[9195,9199],{"text":9196,"type":75,"marks":9197},"Mechanical servicing",[9198],{"type":710},{"text":9200,"type":75}," requires attention to moving parts that experience daily wear. Gate arms, motors, and hydraulic systems need regular inspection for signs of fatigue or damage. You should document all maintenance activities to track performance patterns and predict replacement needs.",{"type":69,"attrs":9202,"content":9203},{"level":1327,"textAlign":6932},[9204],{"text":9205,"type":75,"marks":9206},"Software Updates and Security Protocols",[9207],{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":9209,"content":9210},{"textAlign":6932},[9211],{"text":9212,"type":75},"Your gate security system's digital components require consistent attention. Security patches and firmware updates protect against emerging cyber threats that could compromise access control databases. You should implement automated update scheduling during low-traffic periods to minimize operational disruption.",{"type":112,"attrs":9214,"content":9215},{"textAlign":6932},[9216],{"text":9217,"type":75},"Regular calibration of AI-powered recognition systems maintains accuracy rates above industry standards. Vehicle recognition algorithms benefit from periodic retraining with new license plate formats and vehicle types entering your facility.",{"type":112,"attrs":9219,"content":9220},{"textAlign":6932},[9221],{"text":9222,"type":75},"Temperature monitoring prevents equipment failure in extreme weather conditions, while surge protection safeguards electronic components from power fluctuations that could disable critical security functions.",{"type":69,"attrs":9224,"content":9225},{"level":138,"textAlign":6932},[9226],{"text":9227,"type":75,"marks":9228},"Benefits of Implementing Robust Gate Security Entry Management Systems",[9229],{"type":710},{"type":69,"attrs":9231,"content":9232},{"level":1327,"textAlign":6932},[9233],{"text":9234,"type":75,"marks":9235},"Enhanced Perimeter Security",[9236],{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":9238,"content":9239},{"textAlign":6932},[9240,9244],{"text":9241,"type":75,"marks":9242},"Enhanced perimeter security",[9243],{"type":710},{"text":9245,"type":75}," forms the foundation of effective property protection. Modern gate security entry management systems create multiple layers of defense that significantly reduce security vulnerabilities. You gain complete control over who enters your facility and when, establishing a secure perimeter that deters potential threats before they reach critical areas.",{"type":69,"attrs":9247,"content":9248},{"level":1327,"textAlign":6932},[9249],{"text":9250,"type":75,"marks":9251},"Theft Prevention",[9252],{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":9254,"content":9255},{"textAlign":6932},[9256,9260],{"text":9257,"type":75,"marks":9258},"Theft prevention",[9259],{"type":710},{"text":9261,"type":75}," becomes substantially more effective with comprehensive access controls. These systems maintain detailed records of all entry and exit activities, creating an audit trail that helps identify suspicious patterns. You can implement configurable blacklist engines that proactively detect stolen or unauthorized equipment, reducing cargo theft risk by up to 90% in high-traffic environments.",{"type":69,"attrs":9263,"content":9264},{"level":1327,"textAlign":6932},[9265],{"text":9266,"type":75,"marks":9267},"Efficient Visitor Management",[9268],{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":9270,"content":9271},{"textAlign":6932},[9272,9276],{"text":9273,"type":75,"marks":9274},"Efficient visitor management",[9275],{"type":710},{"text":9277,"type":75}," streamlines your daily operations while maintaining security standards. Time-stamped logs automatically document every interaction, eliminating manual paperwork and reducing processing delays. You can verify visitor credentials through integrated audio/video intercoms, ensuring legitimate access while maintaining detailed records for compliance purposes.",{"type":69,"attrs":9279,"content":9280},{"level":1327,"textAlign":6932},[9281],{"text":9282,"type":75,"marks":9283},"Data-Driven Insights",[9284],{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":9286,"content":9287},{"textAlign":6932},[9288],{"text":9289,"type":75},"Data-driven insights transform your security planning capabilities. Gate security entry management platforms generate comprehensive reports that reveal traffic patterns, peak usage times, and potential security gaps. You can analyze this information to optimize staffing schedules, identify infrastructure needs, and develop proactive security strategies. These analytics help you make informed decisions about future security investments and operational improvements, creating a more resilient and efficient security framework.",{"type":69,"attrs":9291,"content":9292},{"level":138,"textAlign":6932},[9293],{"text":9294,"type":75,"marks":9295},"Challenges in Gate Security Entry Management and How to Overcome Them",[9296],{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":9298,"content":9299},{"textAlign":6932},[9300],{"text":9301,"type":75},"Organizations trying to upgrade their entry management systems face various security challenges. The biggest obstacle is legacy infrastructure, which includes outdated access control panels, incompatible card readers, and separate security databases that don't work together. These fragmented systems make it impossible to monitor in real-time and create dangerous security gaps where unauthorized access can go unnoticed.",{"type":112,"attrs":9303,"content":9304},{"textAlign":6932},[9305],{"text":9306,"type":75},"Technology integration issues make things worse when trying to connect modern solutions with existing hardware. Many facilities struggle with:",{"type":1404,"content":9308},[9309,9320,9331,9342],{"type":1407,"content":9310},[9311],{"type":112,"attrs":9312,"content":9313},{"textAlign":139},[9314,9318],{"text":9315,"type":75,"marks":9316},"Incompatible communication protocols",[9317],{"type":710},{"text":9319,"type":75}," between old and new systems",{"type":1407,"content":9321},[9322],{"type":112,"attrs":9323,"content":9324},{"textAlign":139},[9325,9329],{"text":9326,"type":75,"marks":9327},"Data silos",[9328],{"type":710},{"text":9330,"type":75}," that prevent comprehensive security reporting",{"type":1407,"content":9332},[9333],{"type":112,"attrs":9334,"content":9335},{"textAlign":139},[9336,9340],{"text":9337,"type":75,"marks":9338},"Manual workarounds",[9339],{"type":710},{"text":9341,"type":75}," that increase human error and response times",{"type":1407,"content":9343},[9344],{"type":112,"attrs":9345,"content":9346},{"textAlign":139},[9347,9351],{"text":9348,"type":75,"marks":9349},"Inconsistent user experiences",[9350],{"type":710},{"text":9352,"type":75}," across different entry points",{"type":112,"attrs":9354,"content":9355},{"textAlign":6932},[9356],{"text":9357,"type":75},"Another major challenge is finding the right balance between user convenience and security. When you implement strict security measures, it often creates difficulties for legitimate users, resulting in decreased productivity and frustrated users. What you need are solutions that uphold high security standards without causing operational delays.",{"type":112,"attrs":9359,"content":9360},{"textAlign":6932},[9361,9363,9367,9369,9373,9375,9380],{"text":9362,"type":75},"The best way to overcome these challenges is by using ",{"text":9364,"type":75,"marks":9365},"integrated platforms",[9366],{"type":710},{"text":9368,"type":75},". Modern yard execution platforms like Terminal ",{"text":7427,"type":75,"marks":9370},[9371],{"type":149,"attrs":9372},{"color":1233},{"text":9374,"type":75}," YOS",{"text":9376,"type":75,"marks":9377},"TM",[9378],{"type":9379},"superscript",{"text":9381,"type":75}," offer a solution by providing a complete view of all entry points while seamlessly integrating with existing TMS and WMS systems. These solutions eliminate manual tasks through AI-powered automation, ensuring both effective security and satisfied users through smooth access processes.",{"type":69,"attrs":9383,"content":9384},{"level":138,"textAlign":6932},[9385],{"text":9386,"type":75,"marks":9387},"Future Trends in Gate Security Entry Management",[9388],{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":9390,"content":9391},{"textAlign":6932},[9392,9394,9398],{"text":9393,"type":75},"The world of gate security is changing quickly as ",{"text":9395,"type":75,"marks":9396},"smart yard technology",[9397],{"type":710},{"text":9399,"type":75}," replaces traditional access control methods. The biggest breakthrough is the integration of AI in security systems, where machine learning algorithms can now foresee security threats before they happen. These advanced systems look at visitor behavior, vehicle movements, and access attempts to find irregularities that human operators might overlook.",{"type":69,"attrs":9401,"content":9402},{"level":1327,"textAlign":6932},[9403],{"text":9404,"type":75,"marks":9405},"1. Automated Throughput Enhancement",[9406],{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":9408,"content":9409},{"textAlign":6932},[9410,9412,9416],{"text":9411,"type":75},"The next wave of gate security solutions is driven by ",{"text":9413,"type":75,"marks":9414},"automated throughput enhancement",[9415],{"type":710},{"text":9417,"type":75},". AI-powered yard execution platforms can handle thousands of entry and exit transactions while still following strict security protocols. These systems are expected to cut down average gate processing times by 60-70% and also enhance security accuracy with real-time threat assessments.",{"type":69,"attrs":9419,"content":9420},{"level":1327,"textAlign":6932},[9421],{"text":9422,"type":75,"marks":9423},"2. Data Lakes and Decision Intelligence Platforms",[9424],{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":9426,"content":9427},{"textAlign":6932},[9428],{"text":9429,"type":75},"Data lakes and decision intelligence platforms are changing the way complex entry environments function. These systems collect data from various sources - such as surveillance cameras, access control readers, vehicle recognition systems, and environmental sensors - to create all-encompassing security ecosystems. This technology allows for predictive maintenance scheduling, optimizes traffic flow patterns, and offers useful insights for security planning.",{"type":69,"attrs":9431,"content":9432},{"level":1327,"textAlign":6932},[9433],{"text":9434,"type":75,"marks":9435},"3. Sustainability and Resilience",[9436],{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":9438,"content":9439},{"textAlign":6932},[9440],{"text":9441,"type":75},"Sustainability and resilience are becoming important factors in future gate security implementations. Solar-powered gate systems with battery backup guarantee uninterrupted operation during power outages. Cloud-native structures lessen the need for on-site hardware while offering flexible security solutions that adjust to evolving facility requirements.",{"type":69,"attrs":9443,"content":9444},{"level":1327,"textAlign":6932},[9445],{"text":9446,"type":75,"marks":9447},"4. Integration of Computer Vision Technology",[9448],{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":9450,"content":9451},{"textAlign":6932},[9452],{"text":9453,"type":75},"The combination of computer vision technology with high data accuracy removes the need for manual verification processes. Agentic AI workflows automatically manage routine security decisions, freeing up human security personnel to deal with complicated situations that require judgment and intervention. These advancements lead to self-optimizing security environments that consistently enhance performance through machine learning algorithms.",{"type":69,"attrs":9455,"content":9456},{"level":138,"textAlign":6932},[9457],{"text":2740,"type":75,"marks":9458},[9459],{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":9461,"content":9462},{"textAlign":6932},[9463,9467,9469,9472],{"text":9464,"type":75,"marks":9465},"Secure property access",[9466],{"type":710},{"text":9468,"type":75}," requires more than just traditional lock-and-key solutions. You need comprehensive ",{"text":8953,"type":75,"marks":9470},[9471],{"type":710},{"text":9473,"type":75}," systems that can adapt to your specific operational needs and security challenges.",{"type":112,"attrs":9475,"content":9476},{"textAlign":6932},[9477],{"text":9478,"type":75},"The most effective approach combines multiple technologies into a single framework. Whether you're managing a busy industrial facility or a residential community, your security solution should include:",{"type":1404,"content":9480},[9481,9488,9495,9502],{"type":1407,"content":9482},[9483],{"type":112,"attrs":9484,"content":9485},{"textAlign":139},[9486],{"text":9487,"type":75},"AI-powered surveillance and threat detection",{"type":1407,"content":9489},[9490],{"type":112,"attrs":9491,"content":9492},{"textAlign":139},[9493],{"text":9494,"type":75},"Advanced access control with various credential types",{"type":1407,"content":9496},[9497],{"type":112,"attrs":9498,"content":9499},{"textAlign":139},[9500],{"text":9501,"type":75},"Real-time monitoring and automated response capabilities",{"type":1407,"content":9503},[9504],{"type":112,"attrs":9505,"content":9506},{"textAlign":139},[9507],{"text":9508,"type":75},"Scalable software platforms for centralized management",{"type":112,"attrs":9510,"content":9511},{"textAlign":6932},[9512,9514,9518],{"text":9513,"type":75},"When properly customized to your environment, ",{"text":9515,"type":75,"marks":9516},"integrated gate management solutions",[9517],{"type":710},{"text":9519,"type":75}," can deliver significant results. You'll notice fewer unauthorized entries, smoother visitor processing, and better visibility across your property network.",{"type":112,"attrs":9521,"content":9522},{"textAlign":6932},[9523],{"text":9524,"type":75},"Investing in modern gate security technology will yield benefits such as improved safety, operational efficiency, and data-driven insights. You can't afford to leave your property exposed with outdated systems when there are advanced, scalable solutions readily available.",{"type":112,"attrs":9526,"content":9527},{"textAlign":6932},[9528],{"text":9529,"type":75},"Now is the time to take action. Assess your current security weaknesses and implement technologies that meet the specific requirements of your site for optimal protection and operational effectiveness.",{"id":18,"url":18,"linktype":19,"fieldtype":20,"cached_url":18},[8395],"Gate security entry management is crucial for protecting warehouses, manufacturing facilities, residential communities, and commercial properties throughout North America. With over $50 billion worth of goods being transported daily through more than 50,000 warehouses and factories, it is essential to secure these entry points in order to safeguard valuable assets and ensure smooth operations.",{"id":139,"alt":139,"name":18,"focus":139,"title":139,"source":139,"filename":18,"copyright":139,"fieldtype":1105,"meta_data":9534},{},"Gate Security Management: Systems, Technology & Best Practices",{"id":9537,"alt":18,"name":18,"focus":18,"title":18,"source":18,"filename":9538,"copyright":18,"fieldtype":1105,"meta_data":9539,"is_external_url":49},92495830306412,"/storyblok/f/337048/946x614/8f0e5fe146/k.webp",{},[],"Explore the systems, technology, and best practices behind effective gate security management—improving access control, compliance, and real-time visibility at your facility's entry points.",{"value":2818,"plugin":2819},"gate-security-management-systems-tech-best-practices","all-resources/gate-security-management-systems-tech-best-practices",-670,[4660,4661,4662,2824],"6c82f169-0971-4192-b9b1-e77f84bfab00","2025-09-19T08:47:22.384Z",[],{"name":9551,"created_at":9552,"published_at":9553,"updated_at":9554,"id":9555,"uuid":9556,"content":9557,"slug":10337,"full_slug":10338,"sort_by_date":139,"position":10339,"tag_list":10340,"is_startpage":49,"parent_id":2828,"meta_data":139,"group_id":10341,"first_published_at":10342,"release_id":139,"lang":1161,"path":139,"alternates":10343,"default_full_slug":139,"translated_slugs":139},"Yard Management in Warehousing: Drive Efficiency with Automation","2025-09-19T08:38:08.127Z","2026-03-27T17:43:21.393Z","2026-03-27T17:43:21.414Z",92493775390447,"a4e9fce7-c355-4302-85fe-28bd1ac63208",{"_uid":9558,"body":9559,"link":10324,"title":9551,"author":10325,"excerpt":10327,"category":2808,"is_gated":49,"subtitle":18,"component":2809,"seo_image":10328,"seo_title":9551,"button_text":132,"cover_image":10330,"gated_asset":10334,"seo_noindex":49,"seo_description":10335,"background_color":10336,"featured_in_latest_news":49},"7908fbad-f858-4866-8215-464873f87ec4",{"type":66,"content":9560},[9561,9568,9579,9588,9610,9617,9622,9631,9666,9677,9682,9687,9694,9708,9754,9761,9770,9775,9782,9787,9794,9799,9806,9811,9818,9823,9830,9835,9840,9847,9858,9867,9876,9881,9886,9893,9900,9905,9912,9917,9922,9929,9934,9939,9946,9951,9956,9963,9973,9982,9993,10038,10043,10050,10061,10068,10073,10080,10085,10105,10112,10117,10163,10168,10175,10180,10185,10192,10197,10232,10242,10248,10258,10267,10313],{"type":69,"attrs":9562,"content":9563},{"level":71,"textAlign":6932},[9564],{"text":9565,"type":75,"marks":9566},"Yard Management in the Warehouse: Bridging the Gap Between Highway and Dock",[9567],{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":9569,"content":9570},{"textAlign":6932},[9571,9573,9577],{"text":9572,"type":75},"The yard is a crucial area where highway transportation connects with warehouse operations. However, it is often neglected when it comes to improving ",{"text":9574,"type":75,"marks":9575},"supply chain efficiency",[9576],{"type":710},{"text":9578,"type":75},". While advanced Warehouse Management Systems (WMS) have automated indoor processes and Transportation Management Systems (TMS) have optimized road logistics, the yard still operates as a data black hole between these two highly automated environments.",{"type":112,"attrs":9580,"content":9581},{"textAlign":6932},[9582,9586],{"text":9583,"type":75,"marks":9584},"Yard management in warehouse",[9585],{"type":710},{"text":9587,"type":75}," operations involves coordinating trailer movements, scheduling dock activities, managing gate procedures, and tracking assets within the outdoor areas of the facility. This space is responsible for handling the intricate flow of incoming and outgoing freight, driver check-ins, and strategically positioning trailers to enhance operational efficiency.",{"type":112,"attrs":9589,"content":9590},{"textAlign":6932},[9591,9593,9596,9598,9602,9604,9608],{"text":9592,"type":75},"With over ",{"text":7726,"type":75,"marks":9594},[9595],{"type":710},{"text":9597,"type":75}," being transported every day through more than 50,000 warehouses and factories in North America, the importance of the yard in ",{"text":9599,"type":75,"marks":9600},"warehouse operations",[9601],{"type":710},{"text":9603,"type":75}," has never been greater. The logistics industry is experiencing an unprecedented annual growth of 10% in space requirements, while the working-age population remains unchanged. ",{"text":9605,"type":75,"marks":9606},"Efficient yard management is essential for optimizing supply chain performance",[9607],{"type":710},{"text":9609,"type":75},", acting as the operational link that determines whether your entire logistics network operates smoothly or suffers from expensive delays.",{"type":69,"attrs":9611,"content":9612},{"level":138,"textAlign":6932},[9613],{"text":9614,"type":75,"marks":9615},"Challenges in Traditional Yard Management Practices",[9616],{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":9618,"content":9619},{"textAlign":6932},[9620],{"text":9621,"type":75},"Traditional yard operations across North America's 50,000+ warehouses and factories create significant operational bottlenecks that cost businesses millions in lost productivity. The yard remains a data and technology black hole, even as warehouse management systems and transportation management systems have digitized their respective domains.",{"type":112,"attrs":9623,"content":9624},{"textAlign":6932},[9625,9629],{"text":9626,"type":75,"marks":9627},"Manual processes",[9628],{"type":710},{"text":9630,"type":75}," dominate most yard environments, creating a cascade of inefficiencies:",{"type":1404,"content":9632},[9633,9644,9655],{"type":1407,"content":9634},[9635],{"type":112,"attrs":9636,"content":9637},{"textAlign":139},[9638,9642],{"text":9639,"type":75,"marks":9640},"Yard congestion",[9641],{"type":710},{"text":9643,"type":75}," becomes inevitable when trailers arrive without proper scheduling coordination, leading to traffic jams at gates and around dock doors",{"type":1407,"content":9645},[9646],{"type":112,"attrs":9647,"content":9648},{"textAlign":139},[9649,9653],{"text":9650,"type":75,"marks":9651},"Lack of real-time visibility",[9652],{"type":710},{"text":9654,"type":75}," forces yard personnel to physically search for specific trailers, consuming valuable time and resources",{"type":1407,"content":9656},[9657],{"type":112,"attrs":9658,"content":9659},{"textAlign":139},[9660,9664],{"text":9661,"type":75,"marks":9662},"Communication gaps",[9663],{"type":710},{"text":9665,"type":75}," between carriers and warehouse staff result in missed appointments, delayed departures, and frustrated drivers",{"type":112,"attrs":9667,"content":9668},{"textAlign":6932},[9669,9671,9675],{"text":9670,"type":75},"These ",{"text":9672,"type":75,"marks":9673},"challenges in yard management",[9674],{"type":710},{"text":9676,"type":75}," directly impact your bottom line. When drivers spend excessive time waiting for dock assignments or searching for empty trailers, detention fees accumulate rapidly. Your warehouse staff loses productivity when they can't locate incoming shipments or coordinate outbound loads efficiently.",{"type":112,"attrs":9678,"content":9679},{"textAlign":6932},[9680],{"text":9681,"type":75},"The ripple effects extend beyond immediate costs. Customer satisfaction suffers when shipments face unexpected delays due to yard inefficiencies. Your supply chain resilience weakens as manual coordination struggles to adapt to disruptions or changing priorities. Without automated systems tracking trailer movements and dock utilization, you're operating blind in a critical junction between highway and warehouse operations.",{"type":112,"attrs":9683,"content":9684},{"textAlign":6932},[9685],{"text":9686,"type":75},"To mitigate these issues, adopting advanced solutions such as workforce intellegence can significantly enhance efficiency. These technologies provide real-time visibility into yard operations, streamline communication between stakeholders, and reduce manual processes that lead to bottlenecks.",{"type":69,"attrs":9688,"content":9689},{"level":138,"textAlign":6932},[9690],{"text":9691,"type":75,"marks":9692},"The Role of Yard Management Systems (YMS) in Modern Warehousing",[9693],{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":9695,"content":9696},{"textAlign":6932},[9697,9701,9702,9706],{"text":9698,"type":75,"marks":9699},"Modern",[9700],{"type":710},{"text":103,"type":75},{"text":9703,"type":75,"marks":9704},"Yard Management Systems",[9705],{"type":710},{"text":9707,"type":75}," (YMS) help warehouses and distribution centers manage their yard by replacing inefficient manual processes with automated workflows, providing real-time visibility into all assets, vehicles, and movements within the facility's premises. They should include the following core functionalities:",{"type":1404,"content":9709},[9710,9721,9732,9743],{"type":1407,"content":9711},[9712],{"type":112,"attrs":9713,"content":9714},{"textAlign":139},[9715,9719],{"text":9716,"type":75,"marks":9717},"Real-time tracking:",[9718],{"type":710},{"text":9720,"type":75}," This feature allows you to monitor the locations, statuses, and movements of trailers throughout your entire yard.",{"type":1407,"content":9722},[9723],{"type":112,"attrs":9724,"content":9725},{"textAlign":139},[9726,9730],{"text":9727,"type":75,"marks":9728},"Yard mapping:",[9729],{"type":710},{"text":9731,"type":75}," With yard mapping, you can create digital representations of your facility layout, including dock doors, parking spots, and traffic patterns.",{"type":1407,"content":9733},[9734],{"type":112,"attrs":9735,"content":9736},{"textAlign":139},[9737,9741],{"text":9738,"type":75,"marks":9739},"Gate automation:",[9740],{"type":710},{"text":9742,"type":75}," Gate automation streamlines the check-in and check-out processes by implementing digital workflows.",{"type":1407,"content":9744},[9745],{"type":112,"attrs":9746,"content":9747},{"textAlign":139},[9748,9752],{"text":9749,"type":75,"marks":9750},"Dock appointment scheduling:",[9751],{"type":710},{"text":9753,"type":75}," This functionality helps coordinate inbound and outbound activities to prevent bottlenecks in your operations.",{"type":69,"attrs":9755,"content":9756},{"level":1327,"textAlign":6932},[9757],{"text":9758,"type":75,"marks":9759},"Automation Benefits",[9760],{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":9762,"content":9763},{"textAlign":6932},[9764,9768],{"text":9765,"type":75,"marks":9766},"Automation in yards",[9767],{"type":710},{"text":9769,"type":75}," eliminates the manual processes that create delays and errors. You can now automatically assign parking locations based on load priorities, generate move tasks for spotters, and update carrier notifications without human intervention. This systematic approach should reduce detention fees by more than 20% while improving throughput by over 50%.",{"type":112,"attrs":9771,"content":9772},{"textAlign":6932},[9773],{"text":9774,"type":75},"The technology replaces clipboard-based tracking with digital workflows that capture accurate timestamps, maintain audit trails, and provide instant status updates to all stakeholders. Your yard transforms from a reactive environment into a proactive operation where decisions are made using real-time data rather than assumptions.",{"type":69,"attrs":9776,"content":9777},{"level":138,"textAlign":6932},[9778],{"text":9779,"type":75,"marks":9780},"Benefits of Implementing a Yard Management System",[9781],{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":9783,"content":9784},{"textAlign":6932},[9785],{"text":9786,"type":75},"Implementing a Yard Management System (YMS) offers numerous advantages that go beyond simple automation. It brings about significant improvements in operational efficiency and cost reduction throughout your entire warehouse ecosystem. With modern yard management systems, facilities can now manage trailer movements more effectively, resulting in increased productivity across the supply chain.",{"type":69,"attrs":9788,"content":9789},{"level":1327,"textAlign":6932},[9790],{"text":9791,"type":75,"marks":9792},"Increased Throughput",[9793],{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":9795,"content":9796},{"textAlign":6932},[9797],{"text":9798,"type":75},"One of the key benefits you'll gain from using a YMS is higher throughput. Advanced YMS platforms optimize trailer movements by intelligently routing vehicles to the most suitable dock doors based on factors such as load priority, delivery schedules, and dock availability. This coordinated approach eliminates the uncertainty that often leads to congestion and delays. By implementing AI-powered yard solutions that automate gate processes and seamlessly coordinate yard activities, you can expect to see an improvement of over 50% in throughput.",{"type":69,"attrs":9800,"content":9801},{"level":1327,"textAlign":6932},[9802],{"text":9803,"type":75,"marks":9804},"Improved Dock Utilization",[9805],{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":9807,"content":9808},{"textAlign":6932},[9809],{"text":9810,"type":75},"Intelligent scheduling algorithms play a crucial role in maximizing dock utilization. Your YMS continuously analyzes how dock doors are used, identifying opportunities to increase capacity while minimizing idle time. This data-driven approach ensures that every dock door operates at its best throughout your operational hours.",{"type":69,"attrs":9812,"content":9813},{"level":1327,"textAlign":6932},[9814],{"text":9815,"type":75,"marks":9816},"Cost Savings on Detention and Demurrage Fees",[9817],{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":9819,"content":9820},{"textAlign":6932},[9821],{"text":9822,"type":75},"By implementing better scheduling capabilities through YMS, you can expect immediate financial benefits in the form of reduced detention and demurrage fees. With faster processing of carriers, drivers will spend less time waiting in your yard, resulting in lower costs for your business. Companies that have integrated comprehensive yard management into their warehouse operations typically experience a 12% decrease in driver detention fees thanks to automated workflows that speed up check-in and check-out processes.",{"type":69,"attrs":9824,"content":9825},{"level":1327,"textAlign":6932},[9826],{"text":9827,"type":75,"marks":9828},"Proactive Decision-Making with Real-Time Visibility",[9829],{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":9831,"content":9832},{"textAlign":6932},[9833],{"text":9834,"type":75},"Having real-time visibility into yard operations allows you to make proactive decisions and prevent bottlenecks before they negatively impact your bottom line. By being able to see what's happening in your yard at any given moment, you can address issues promptly and keep things running smoothly.",{"type":112,"attrs":9836,"content":9837},{"textAlign":6932},[9838],{"text":9839,"type":75},"These benefits demonstrate how implementing a Yard Management System can greatly enhance your warehouse operations, leading to increased efficiency and cost savings throughout your supply chain.",{"type":69,"attrs":9841,"content":9842},{"level":138,"textAlign":6932},[9843],{"text":9844,"type":75,"marks":9845},"Integration of YMS with Other Supply Chain Technologies for Enhanced Visibility",[9846],{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":9848,"content":9849},{"textAlign":6932},[9850,9852,9856],{"text":9851,"type":75},"Modern yard operations cannot exist in isolation. ",{"text":9853,"type":75,"marks":9854},"WMS integration",[9855],{"type":710},{"text":9857,"type":75}," creates a seamless bridge between your yard activities and warehouse floor operations, enabling real-time data synchronization that eliminates manual handoffs and reduces errors. When your yard management system communicates directly with your warehouse management system, you gain immediate visibility into dock door availability, inventory status, and processing priorities.",{"type":112,"attrs":9859,"content":9860},{"textAlign":6932},[9861,9865],{"text":9862,"type":75,"marks":9863},"TMS integration",[9864],{"type":710},{"text":9866,"type":75}," extends this connectivity to your transportation network, allowing carriers to receive automated updates about dock assignments, wait times, and departure schedules. This integration transforms fragmented communication into a unified data flow that keeps all stakeholders informed and aligned.",{"type":112,"attrs":9868,"content":9869},{"textAlign":6932},[9870,9874],{"text":9871,"type":75,"marks":9872},"ERP connectivity",[9873],{"type":710},{"text":9875,"type":75}," completes the digital ecosystem by linking yard operations to your broader business processes. Financial systems receive automated updates about detention fees, while procurement teams gain visibility into supplier performance metrics directly from yard data.",{"type":112,"attrs":9877,"content":9878},{"textAlign":6932},[9879],{"text":9880,"type":75},"The power of integrated platforms becomes evident when you consider the ripple effects of yard decisions. A delayed inbound trailer doesn't just impact the yard—it affects warehouse labor scheduling, outbound shipment timing, and customer delivery commitments. Integrated systems ensure these dependencies are visible and manageable across your entire operation.",{"type":112,"attrs":9882,"content":9883},{"textAlign":6932},[9884],{"text":9885,"type":75},"You achieve true end-to-end visibility when yard data flows seamlessly between systems, creating a single source of truth that eliminates information silos and enables proactive decision-making across warehouse and transportation functions.",{"type":69,"attrs":9887,"content":9888},{"level":138,"textAlign":6932},[9889],{"text":9890,"type":75,"marks":9891},"Advanced Technologies Shaping the Future of Yard Management",[9892],{"type":710},{"type":69,"attrs":9894,"content":9895},{"level":1327,"textAlign":6932},[9896],{"text":9897,"type":75,"marks":9898},"Artificial Intelligence (AI) in Yards",[9899],{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":9901,"content":9902},{"textAlign":6932},[9903],{"text":9904,"type":75},"AI is transforming traditional yard operations by introducing advanced automation capabilities. One key application of AI in yards is license plate recognition technology, which eliminates the need for manual data entry at gate checkpoints. With this technology, trucks can pass through the gates without stopping, as the system automatically captures and processes vehicle information. This advancement significantly reduces gate processing time from several minutes to just a few seconds, resulting in a substantial increase in the number of vehicles that can be processed during busy periods.",{"type":69,"attrs":9906,"content":9907},{"level":1327,"textAlign":6932},[9908],{"text":9909,"type":75,"marks":9910},"Computer Vision Technology",[9911],{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":9913,"content":9914},{"textAlign":6932},[9915],{"text":9916,"type":75},"Another area where technology is making a significant impact is through computer vision. This technology goes beyond simple identification tasks and offers comprehensive monitoring capabilities. By using advanced camera systems equipped with AI algorithms, yards can now automatically identify different types of carriers, detect any damage to equipment, and ensure compliance with safety protocols.",{"type":112,"attrs":9918,"content":9919},{"textAlign":6932},[9920],{"text":9921,"type":75},"One of the major benefits of computer vision technology is its ability to track trailer movements throughout the entire yard without any human involvement. This means that yard managers can receive real-time alerts whenever assets deviate from their designated paths or remain stationary for longer than expected.",{"type":69,"attrs":9923,"content":9924},{"level":1327,"textAlign":6932},[9925],{"text":9926,"type":75,"marks":9927},"Smart Yard Solutions",[9928],{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":9930,"content":9931},{"textAlign":6932},[9932],{"text":9933,"type":75},"In addition to AI and computer vision, yards are also benefiting from smart yard solutions that utilize machine learning algorithms. These solutions aim to optimize parking assignments and predict equipment needs based on historical patterns.",{"type":112,"attrs":9935,"content":9936},{"textAlign":6932},[9937],{"text":9938,"type":75},"By analyzing past data, these systems can recommend the most efficient positioning for trailers, resulting in a reduction of up to 40% in spotter truck movements. Furthermore, computer vision applications integrated into these smart yard solutions enable automatic detection of unauthorized vehicles, missing equipment, and potential security breaches.",{"type":69,"attrs":9940,"content":9941},{"level":1327,"textAlign":6932},[9942],{"text":9943,"type":75,"marks":9944},"The Power of Modern AI-Powered Platforms",[9945],{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":9947,"content":9948},{"textAlign":6932},[9949],{"text":9950,"type":75},"The combination of AI, computer vision, and machine learning has led to the development of modern platforms that are capable of achieving an impressive near-perfect accuracy rate in asset identification and tracking. This level of precision eliminates any guesswork that was common in traditional yard management practices.",{"type":112,"attrs":9952,"content":9953},{"textAlign":6932},[9954],{"text":9955,"type":75},"What makes these technologies even more appealing is their ability to be deployed through modular hardware solutions. These solutions can easily integrate with existing infrastructure without requiring extensive IT resources or causing disruptions to ongoing operations. As a result, yards can expect immediate improvements in their day-to-day operations across their entire network.",{"type":69,"attrs":9957,"content":9958},{"level":138,"textAlign":6932},[9959],{"text":9960,"type":75,"marks":9961},"Best Practices for Effective Yard Management Implementation",[9962],{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":9964,"content":9965},{"textAlign":6932},[9966,9967,9971],{"text":8196,"type":75},{"text":9968,"type":75,"marks":9969},"yard automation best practices",[9970],{"type":710},{"text":9972,"type":75}," begin with strategic gate automation that eliminates manual check-in bottlenecks. You should implement automated gate systems that capture carrier information, validate appointments, and direct drivers to designated staging areas without human intervention. This approach reduces processing time from 15 minutes to under 2 minutes per transaction.",{"type":112,"attrs":9974,"content":9975},{"textAlign":6932},[9976,9980],{"text":9977,"type":75,"marks":9978},"Asset tracking methods",[9979],{"type":710},{"text":9981,"type":75}," form the backbone of modern yard operations. Computer vision cameras provide the most comprehensive solution, delivering 99%+ accuracy in identifying trailers, containers, and equipment across your facility. These systems automatically capture license plates, DOT numbers, and equipment specifications while monitoring asset movements in real-time.",{"type":112,"attrs":9983,"content":9984},{"textAlign":6932},[9985,9987,9991],{"text":9986,"type":75},"For enhanced precision in ",{"text":9988,"type":75,"marks":9989},"yard management in warehouse",[9990],{"type":710},{"text":9992,"type":75}," operations, you can deploy multiple tracking technologies:",{"type":1404,"content":9994},[9995,10006,10017,10027],{"type":1407,"content":9996},[9997],{"type":112,"attrs":9998,"content":9999},{"textAlign":139},[10000,10004],{"text":10001,"type":75,"marks":10002},"RFID tags",[10003],{"type":710},{"text":10005,"type":75}," on trailers enable automated inventory updates as assets move through designated checkpoints",{"type":1407,"content":10007},[10008],{"type":112,"attrs":10009,"content":10010},{"textAlign":139},[10011,10015],{"text":10012,"type":75,"marks":10013},"Bluetooth beacons",[10014],{"type":710},{"text":10016,"type":75}," provide continuous location data for mobile equipment like yard trucks and hostlers",{"type":1407,"content":10018},[10019],{"type":112,"attrs":10020,"content":10021},{"textAlign":139},[10022,10025],{"text":4625,"type":75,"marks":10023},[10024],{"type":710},{"text":10026,"type":75}," monitor trailer temperatures, door status, and security conditions",{"type":1407,"content":10028},[10029],{"type":112,"attrs":10030,"content":10031},{"textAlign":139},[10032,10036],{"text":10033,"type":75,"marks":10034},"Wireless cameras",[10035],{"type":710},{"text":10037,"type":75}," offer flexible monitoring in areas where permanent installations aren't feasible",{"type":112,"attrs":10039,"content":10040},{"textAlign":6932},[10041],{"text":10042,"type":75},"Gate routing automation directs incoming carriers to optimal parking locations based on load priority, dock availability, and departure schedules. You should configure your system to automatically assign spots that minimize travel distances and prevent congestion during peak hours. Smart routing algorithms can reduce average yard dwell time by 30-40% while maximizing dock door utilization rates.",{"type":69,"attrs":10044,"content":10045},{"level":138,"textAlign":6932},[10046],{"text":10047,"type":75,"marks":10048},"Measuring Success in Yard Operations: Key Performance Indicators (KPIs) to Monitor",[10049],{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":10051,"content":10052},{"textAlign":6932},[10053,10055,10059],{"text":10054,"type":75},"Tracking the right ",{"text":10056,"type":75,"marks":10057},"KPIs in yard management",[10058],{"type":710},{"text":10060,"type":75}," transforms your operational visibility from guesswork into data-driven decision making. You need specific metrics that directly correlate with your bottom line and operational efficiency.",{"type":69,"attrs":10062,"content":10063},{"level":1327,"textAlign":6932},[10064],{"text":10065,"type":75,"marks":10066},"Primary KPIs for Yard Operations",[10067],{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":10069,"content":10070},{"textAlign":6932},[10071],{"text":10072,"type":75},"Truck turnaround time stands as your primary performance indicator. This metric measures the total time from when a truck enters your gate until it exits. Industry leaders achieve turnaround times under 45 minutes, while traditional operations often struggle with 2-3 hour cycles. You can break this down further by measuring gate processing time, dock assignment delays, and loading/unloading duration.",{"type":69,"attrs":10074,"content":10075},{"level":1327,"textAlign":6932},[10076],{"text":10077,"type":75,"marks":10078},"Supporting KPIs for Yard Operations",[10079],{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":10081,"content":10082},{"textAlign":6932},[10083],{"text":10084,"type":75},"In addition to truck turnaround time, there are several supporting KPIs that can provide valuable insights into your yard operations:",{"type":1404,"content":10086},[10087,10098],{"type":1407,"content":10088},[10089],{"type":112,"attrs":10090,"content":10091},{"textAlign":139},[10092,10096],{"text":10093,"type":75,"marks":10094},"Dock door utilization rate",[10095],{"type":710},{"text":10097,"type":75}," reveals how effectively you're maximizing your physical infrastructure. Calculate this by dividing active dock hours by total available dock hours. High-performing facilities maintain 75-85% utilization rates during peak hours.",{"type":1407,"content":10099},[10100],{"type":112,"attrs":10101,"content":10102},{"textAlign":139},[10103],{"text":10104,"type":75},"Detention time reduction directly impacts your carrier relationships and operational costs. Track both average detention time per carrier and total detention fees paid monthly. Modern yard management systems help reduce detention fees by 12% through optimized scheduling and automated workflows.",{"type":69,"attrs":10106,"content":10107},{"level":1327,"textAlign":6932},[10108],{"text":10109,"type":75,"marks":10110},"Additional Metrics to Monitor",[10111],{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":10113,"content":10114},{"textAlign":6932},[10115],{"text":10116,"type":75},"These additional metrics can further enhance your understanding of yard performance:",{"type":1404,"content":10118},[10119,10130,10141,10152],{"type":1407,"content":10120},[10121],{"type":112,"attrs":10122,"content":10123},{"textAlign":139},[10124,10128],{"text":10125,"type":75,"marks":10126},"Asset search time",[10127],{"type":710},{"text":10129,"type":75}," - Track how quickly staff locate trailers and containers",{"type":1407,"content":10131},[10132],{"type":112,"attrs":10133,"content":10134},{"textAlign":139},[10135,10139],{"text":10136,"type":75,"marks":10137},"Gate processing accuracy",[10138],{"type":710},{"text":10140,"type":75}," - Measure data entry errors and processing delays",{"type":1407,"content":10142},[10143],{"type":112,"attrs":10144,"content":10145},{"textAlign":139},[10146,10150],{"text":10147,"type":75,"marks":10148},"Parking space optimization",[10149],{"type":710},{"text":10151,"type":75}," - Monitor space utilization and staging efficiency",{"type":1407,"content":10153},[10154],{"type":112,"attrs":10155,"content":10156},{"textAlign":139},[10157,10161],{"text":10158,"type":75,"marks":10159},"Carrier compliance rates",[10160],{"type":710},{"text":10162,"type":75}," - Track appointment adherence and documentation accuracy",{"type":112,"attrs":10164,"content":10165},{"textAlign":6932},[10166],{"text":10167,"type":75},"These metrics provide the foundation for continuous improvement in your yard operations.",{"type":69,"attrs":10169,"content":10170},{"level":138,"textAlign":6932},[10171],{"text":10172,"type":75,"marks":10173},"The Future of Yard Management in Warehousing: Embracing Digitization and Automation Growth",[10174],{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":10176,"content":10177},{"textAlign":6932},[10178],{"text":10179,"type":75},"The future trends in yard management indicate significant technological advancements, with AI-driven automation taking the lead. While Warehouse Management Systems and Transportation Management Systems have successfully digitized their respective areas, the yard has remained a major data blind spot—a gap that's quickly closing as organizations realize the urgent need for complete visibility across their entire supply chain.",{"type":112,"attrs":10181,"content":10182},{"textAlign":6932},[10183],{"text":10184,"type":75},"AI-powered computer vision technology is transforming how yards operate, delivering 99.5% data accuracy and enabling fully automated gate processes. These systems can identify license plates, detect equipment damage, and coordinate complex yard movements without human involvement. The scalability potential is enormous—organizations with multiple facilities can deploy unified platforms that provide single-pane-of-glass visibility across their entire yard network.",{"type":69,"attrs":10186,"content":10187},{"level":1327,"textAlign":6932},[10188],{"text":10189,"type":75,"marks":10190},"Environmental Impact and Sustainability Benefits",[10191],{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":10193,"content":10194},{"textAlign":6932},[10195],{"text":10196,"type":75},"Smart yard technologies directly support sustainability initiatives by:",{"type":1404,"content":10198},[10199,10210,10221],{"type":1407,"content":10200},[10201],{"type":112,"attrs":10202,"content":10203},{"textAlign":139},[10204,10208],{"text":10205,"type":75,"marks":10206},"Reducing truck idle times ",[10207],{"type":710},{"text":10209,"type":75},"through optimized scheduling and automated check-in processes",{"type":1407,"content":10211},[10212],{"type":112,"attrs":10213,"content":10214},{"textAlign":139},[10215,10219],{"text":10216,"type":75,"marks":10217},"Minimizing emissions",[10218],{"type":710},{"text":10220,"type":75}," from unnecessary vehicle movements and extended detention periods",{"type":1407,"content":10222},[10223],{"type":112,"attrs":10224,"content":10225},{"textAlign":139},[10226,10230],{"text":10227,"type":75,"marks":10228},"Improving fuel efficiency",[10229],{"type":710},{"text":10231,"type":75}," by eliminating driver confusion and reducing search times for assets",{"type":112,"attrs":10233,"content":10234},{"textAlign":6932},[10235,10236,10240],{"text":3884,"type":75},{"text":10237,"type":75,"marks":10238},"closing of the digitization gap",[10239],{"type":710},{"text":10241,"type":75}," represents more than just operational efficiency—it's about building resilient supply chains capable of handling increasing demand while being environmentally responsible. Companies implementing comprehensive yard digitization report 50%+ throughput improvements and 90% reduction in asset search times, demonstrating the transformative potential of these technologies.",{"type":69,"attrs":10243,"content":10244},{"level":138,"textAlign":6932},[10245],{"text":2740,"type":75,"marks":10246},[10247],{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":10249,"content":10250},{"textAlign":6932},[10251,10253,10256],{"text":10252,"type":75},"The transformation of ",{"text":9988,"type":75,"marks":10254},[10255],{"type":710},{"text":10257,"type":75}," operations represents one of the most significant opportunities for operational excellence in today's supply chain landscape. You've seen how traditional yard practices create bottlenecks that ripple through entire logistics networks, while modern Yard Management Systems deliver measurable improvements in throughput, cost reduction, and operational visibility.",{"type":112,"attrs":10259,"content":10260},{"textAlign":6932},[10261,10265],{"text":10262,"type":75,"marks":10263},"Mid-market and large enterprises",[10264],{"type":710},{"text":10266,"type":75}," can no longer afford to treat their yards as operational afterthoughts. The data is clear: companies implementing comprehensive yard digitization achieve:",{"type":1404,"content":10268},[10269,10280,10291,10302],{"type":1407,"content":10270},[10271],{"type":112,"attrs":10272,"content":10273},{"textAlign":139},[10274,10278],{"text":10275,"type":75,"marks":10276},"50%+ throughput improvements",[10277],{"type":710},{"text":10279,"type":75}," through automated workflows",{"type":1407,"content":10281},[10282],{"type":112,"attrs":10283,"content":10284},{"textAlign":139},[10285,10289],{"text":10286,"type":75,"marks":10287},"90% reduction in asset search time",[10288],{"type":710},{"text":10290,"type":75}," with AI-powered tracking",{"type":1407,"content":10292},[10293],{"type":112,"attrs":10294,"content":10295},{"textAlign":139},[10296,10300],{"text":10297,"type":75,"marks":10298},"20%+ reduction in driver detention fees",[10299],{"type":710},{"text":10301,"type":75}," through optimized scheduling",{"type":1407,"content":10303},[10304],{"type":112,"attrs":10305,"content":10306},{"textAlign":139},[10307,10311],{"text":10308,"type":75,"marks":10309},"Rapid ROI ",[10310],{"type":710},{"text":10312,"type":75},"in under 5 months",{"type":112,"attrs":10314,"content":10315},{"textAlign":6932},[10316,10318,10322],{"text":10317,"type":75},"Your yard serves as the critical bridge between highway and warehouse operations. By prioritizing digitization initiatives, you position your organization to capture competitive advantages that compound across your entire logistics network. The question isn't whether to modernize your yard operations—it's how quickly you can implement the right ",{"text":10319,"type":75,"marks":10320},"yard management systems",[10321],{"type":710},{"text":10323,"type":75}," to unlock these transformative benefits.",{"id":18,"url":18,"linktype":19,"fieldtype":20,"cached_url":18},[10326],"0ac1d78f-1a4b-4d93-a889-41d789dacbd4","The yard is a crucial area where highway transportation connects with warehouse operations. However, it is often neglected when it comes to improving supply chain efficiency. While advanced Warehouse Management Systems (WMS) have automated indoor processes and Transportation Management Systems (TMS) have optimized road logistics, the yard still operates as a data black hole between these two highly automated environments.",{"id":139,"alt":139,"name":18,"focus":139,"title":139,"source":139,"filename":18,"copyright":139,"fieldtype":1105,"meta_data":10329},{},{"id":10331,"alt":18,"name":18,"focus":18,"title":18,"source":18,"filename":10332,"copyright":18,"fieldtype":1105,"meta_data":10333,"is_external_url":49},92493894565308,"/storyblok/f/337048/1866x1194/72ca184fd1/f.webp",{},[],"Learn how automation is transforming yard management in warehousing—streamlining trailer flow, reducing manual tasks, and improving dock coordination for faster, more efficient operations.",{"value":2818,"plugin":2819},"yard-management-in-warehousing-drive-efficiency-with-automation","all-resources/yard-management-in-warehousing-drive-efficiency-with-automation",-650,[4662,2824,2825,2826],"f822b772-ca35-4464-a123-4f4dc89af31a","2025-09-19T08:39:56.256Z",[],{"name":10345,"created_at":10346,"published_at":10347,"updated_at":10348,"id":10349,"uuid":10350,"content":10351,"slug":10673,"full_slug":10674,"sort_by_date":139,"position":10675,"tag_list":10676,"is_startpage":49,"parent_id":2828,"meta_data":139,"group_id":10680,"first_published_at":10681,"release_id":139,"lang":1161,"path":139,"alternates":10682,"default_full_slug":139,"translated_slugs":139},"If trust in freight is dead, why is it still running the yard?","2026-06-17T23:32:37.997Z","2026-06-17T23:46:56.455Z","2026-06-17T23:46:56.471Z",188618989585127,"2202c3e1-77d8-4df4-bda3-fded1fb95034",{"_uid":10352,"body":10353,"link":10659,"title":10345,"author":10660,"excerpt":10662,"category":2808,"is_gated":49,"subtitle":18,"component":2809,"seo_image":10663,"seo_title":10665,"button_text":132,"cover_image":10666,"gated_asset":10670,"seo_noindex":49,"seo_description":10671,"background_color":10672,"featured_in_latest_news":49},"2e214bba-8b06-4181-85d1-edd14859a052",{"type":66,"content":10354},[10355,10363,10371,10451,10459,10467,10475,10483,10491,10499,10507,10515,10523,10531,10539,10547,10555,10563,10571,10579,10587,10595,10603,10611,10619,10627,10635,10643,10651],{"type":112,"attrs":10356,"content":10357},{"textAlign":139},[10358],{"text":10359,"type":75,"marks":10360},"I’ve been in the supply chain industry for 30 years. For the past decade or so, as new software solutions flooded the market, anyone who knew “how things really operated,” knew it was an industry run on relationships. Technology was just a supplement to how money, data and freight got moved from A to B. Even with our current AI gold rush, there are still industry veterans who remember faxing bills of lading and are still working with those same colleagues. I’d argue the foundation of the industry – trust, mutual respect, familiarity – has eroded to a point of no return. Not because of technology, but because of prolific freight fraud that has fostered a culture of paranoia across the industry. And as a veteran of yard technology and systems, I can tell you a lot of this distrust starts in the yard. ",[10361],{"type":149,"attrs":10362},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":10364,"content":10365},{"textAlign":139},[10366],{"text":10367,"type":75,"marks":10368},"Walk into almost any logistics facility in the country and you'll find the same scene at the gate: a person with a tablet or a clipboard. They typically don’t have any information on the trucks coming in – is this the carrier we booked? Is this driver legit? Is that the right trailer, sealed the way it left the last yard? Security and visibility solutions have helped operators answer those questions across almost every node of the supply chain, but in the yard, carrier verification and security is about as sophisticated as the check out process at Costco. ",[10369],{"type":149,"attrs":10370},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":10372,"content":10373},{"textAlign":139},[10374,10379,10391,10396,10405,10410,10418,10423,10432,10437,10446],{"text":10375,"type":75,"marks":10376},"Cargo theft across the U.S. and Canada ",[10377],{"type":149,"attrs":10378},{"color":1233},{"text":10380,"type":75,"marks":10381},"climbed past $725 million last year",[10382,10386,10389],{"type":10383,"attrs":10384},"link",{"href":10385,"uuid":139,"anchor":139,"target":139,"linktype":96},"https://www.cargonet.com/news-and-events/cargonet-in-the-media/2025-theft-trends/",{"type":149,"attrs":10387},{"color":10388},"#1155CC",{"type":10390},"underline",{"text":10392,"type":75,"marks":10393},", a 60% jump, and the fastest-growing vector isn't the smash-and-grab. It's ",[10394],{"type":149,"attrs":10395},{"color":1233},{"text":10397,"type":75,"marks":10398},"fraud",[10399,10402,10404],{"type":10383,"attrs":10400},{"href":10401,"uuid":139,"anchor":139,"target":139,"linktype":96},"https://www.ic3.gov/PSA/2026/PSA260430",{"type":149,"attrs":10403},{"color":10388},{"type":10390},{"text":10406,"type":75,"marks":10407},": fictitious pickups, stolen identities, carriers that look legitimate on a load board and vanish with a full trailer. The FBI has ",[10408],{"type":149,"attrs":10409},{"color":1233},{"text":10411,"type":75,"marks":10412},"said plainly",[10413,10415,10417],{"type":10383,"attrs":10414},{"href":10401,"uuid":139,"anchor":139,"target":139,"linktype":96},{"type":149,"attrs":10416},{"color":10388},{"type":10390},{"text":10419,"type":75,"marks":10420}," that impersonation is now the dominant way freight gets stolen. And people like the veteran gate guard who knew every regular driver by name is retiring. ",[10421],{"type":149,"attrs":10422},{"color":1233},{"text":10424,"type":75,"marks":10425},"Warehouse turnover sits near 50%",[10426,10429,10431],{"type":10383,"attrs":10427},{"href":10428,"uuid":139,"anchor":139,"target":139,"linktype":96},"https://www.bls.gov/news.release/pdf/jolts.pdf",{"type":149,"attrs":10430},{"color":10388},{"type":10390},{"text":10433,"type":75,"marks":10434},"; for long-haul drivers it's",[10435],{"type":149,"attrs":10436},{"color":1233},{"text":10438,"type":75,"marks":10439}," above 90%",[10440,10443,10445],{"type":10383,"attrs":10441},{"href":10442,"uuid":139,"anchor":139,"target":139,"linktype":96},"https://www.ooida.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/The-Churn-A-Brief-Look-at-the-Roots-of-High-Driver-Turnover-in-U.S.-Trucking.pdf",{"type":149,"attrs":10444},{"color":10388},{"type":10390},{"text":10447,"type":75,"marks":10448},". ",[10449],{"type":149,"attrs":10450},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":10452,"content":10453},{"textAlign":139},[10454],{"text":10455,"type":75,"marks":10456},"So we have a place where every load in the supply chain physically changes hands, where legal custody transfers, where accurate information is scarce or absent, where information asymmetry is accelerating fraud, and where the human safety net is thinning. And it remains the one part of the chain we never really invested in. Go figure. ",[10457],{"type":149,"attrs":10458},{"color":1233},{"type":69,"attrs":10460,"content":10461},{"level":138,"textAlign":139},[10462],{"text":10463,"type":75,"marks":10464},"Yard security is, in fact, the warehouse’s problem ",[10465],{"type":149,"attrs":10466},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":10468,"content":10469},{"textAlign":139},[10470],{"text":10471,"type":75,"marks":10472},"When a load is stolen through fraud, the strategic theft completes at the moment the trailer is released. The facility that released it is the one left holding the liability. The contractual and compliance obligations that increasingly govern freight (documented carrier vetting, verified driver identity, conveyance inspection, an unbroken chain-of-custody record) all point back to the gate that let the truck through.",[10473],{"type":149,"attrs":10474},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":10476,"content":10477},{"textAlign":139},[10478],{"text":10479,"type":75,"marks":10480},"Today, cargo insurers, customer contracts, and programs like CTPAT increasingly demand records that paper-based yards cannot produce, and that a gate workforce turning over every eighteen months cannot reliably capture by hand. Yard security is, in fact, the warehouse’s problem, and it has to be solved at the gate, inside the system that runs it, because that's where custody actually changes and where the record either gets made or gets lost.",[10481],{"type":149,"attrs":10482},{"color":1233},{"type":69,"attrs":10484,"content":10485},{"level":138,"textAlign":139},[10486],{"text":10487,"type":75,"marks":10488},"No one owns the yard (and that’s a problem)",[10489],{"type":149,"attrs":10490},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":10492,"content":10493},{"textAlign":139},[10494],{"text":10495,"type":75,"marks":10496},"I got my first IT job at a 3PL in the early 1990s. It's tempting to say the yard security problem is about bad software, that the industry tried to secure the yard and the tools weren't good enough. But back then the operations team was more worried about people jumping the fence, cutting the seal, and throwing product back over. Technology wasn't available, so companies threw bodies at it.",[10497],{"type":149,"attrs":10498},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":10500,"content":10501},{"textAlign":139},[10502],{"text":10503,"type":75,"marks":10504},"Yard management software was built for operations and throughput: dock assignments, dwell time, trailer locations, getting trucks in and out efficiently. Security, identity, and chain of custody were understood as separate concerns, owned by separate people, and addressed, when they were addressed at all, by separate means. This is why most facilities outsource the gate to a security company. Some of it got handled by point solutions bolted on from the outside: carrier-vetting services, cameras, physical ID checks by a guy named Steve. A lot of it wasn't handled by software at all.",[10505],{"type":149,"attrs":10506},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":10508,"content":10509},{"textAlign":139},[10510],{"text":10511,"type":75,"marks":10512},"The result is a set of capabilities that have always lived in paper documentation and verbal communication over a radio – silos – disconnected from each other and from the system that actually runs the yard. For example, the camera never knew who the driver was, the carrier check never reached the gate, and the custody record, where it existed, sat in a binder. None of these pieces were wrong on their own. They simply were never brought together, because for most of the industry's history there was no obvious reason to make changes. ",[10513],{"type":149,"attrs":10514},{"color":1233},{"type":69,"attrs":10516,"content":10517},{"level":138,"textAlign":139},[10518],{"text":10519,"type":75,"marks":10520},"The lesser of two evils",[10521],{"type":149,"attrs":10522},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":10524,"content":10525},{"textAlign":139},[10526],{"text":10527,"type":75,"marks":10528},"For most of its history, buying yard technology meant choosing between two unsatisfying options, and the choice had nothing to do with security. It was just the shape of the market.",[10529],{"type":149,"attrs":10530},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":10532,"content":10533},{"textAlign":139},[10534],{"text":10535,"type":75,"marks":10536},"The first option was the large enterprise platform that promised end-to-end control of everything. In practice it was a clunky, glorified system of record: an expensive license, a six month deployment, zero flexibility. It promised comprehensive coverage yet could not change with the business without a massive change request and a matching invoice. You got breadth, and you paid for it in cost and rigidity.",[10537],{"type":149,"attrs":10538},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":10540,"content":10541},{"textAlign":139},[10542],{"text":10543,"type":75,"marks":10544},"The second was the point solution, with the opposite promise: do one thing exceptionally well. Many genuinely deliver. But when every capability comes from a different vendor, the buyer inherits subscriptions, logins, dashboards, data formats, and renewal cycles, none of which speak to one another. Someone has to integrate them, monitor them, reconcile their outputs, and re-buy them every year. You got depth, and you paid for it in fragmentation.",[10545],{"type":149,"attrs":10546},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":10548,"content":10549},{"textAlign":139},[10550],{"text":10551,"type":75,"marks":10552},"So that was the trade. Breadth or depth. One expensive, rigid system or ten sharp tools that don't talk. For decades there was no third answer, and no reason to expect one.",[10553],{"type":149,"attrs":10554},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":10556,"content":10557},{"textAlign":139},[10558],{"text":10559,"type":75,"marks":10560},"AI-native development is the third answer. Capabilities that once demanded a specialized enterprise stack and a year of integration can now be built and deployed in a fraction of the time, at a fraction of the cost. You no longer choose between breadth and depth, or between flexibility and cohesion. You can have technology that does many things at once, changes with the business, and doesn't break the bank or trigger a year of change management.",[10561],{"type":149,"attrs":10562},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":10564,"content":10565},{"textAlign":139},[10566],{"text":10567,"type":75,"marks":10568},"That is what makes this moment matter for the yard. Once the tradeoff collapses, capabilities that used to demand entirely separate systems can finally live in one. And the two that most need to come together are yard management and yard security, domains that were always treated as separate concerns, owned by separate people, bought from separate vendors. For the first time, there is no reason they have to be.",[10569],{"type":149,"attrs":10570},{"color":1233},{"type":69,"attrs":10572,"content":10573},{"level":138,"textAlign":139},[10574],{"text":10575,"type":75,"marks":10576},"Security should live inside the system already running the gate ",[10577],{"type":149,"attrs":10578},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":10580,"content":10581},{"textAlign":139},[10582],{"text":10583,"type":75,"marks":10584},"For the first time, the technology exists to create a modular layer inside the system that already runs the yard. The capabilities that secure a yard (knowing the carrier, verifying the driver, watching the perimeter, documenting what actually leaves) no longer have to be a stack of disconnected point tools or a separate enterprise security program.",[10585],{"type":149,"attrs":10586},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":10588,"content":10589},{"textAlign":139},[10590],{"text":10591,"type":75,"marks":10592},"We’re seeing a great convergence: yard security and yard management becoming one single entity. And AI has made it feasible to build something modular and affordable that does both at once.",[10593],{"type":149,"attrs":10594},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":10596,"content":10597},{"textAlign":139},[10598],{"text":10599,"type":75,"marks":10600},"Secondarily, we’re able to address both yard security and management because the data is the same data. For example, the check-in event and the security event are not two events; they are one event seen from two angles. The instant a truck reaches the gate, the system logging it for operations already holds nearly everything security needs, such as who is driving, what they are hauling, what the camera sees, and exactly when it happened. Recording that as an operations entry over here and a security entry over there was never a principle of good design.",[10601],{"type":149,"attrs":10602},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":10604,"content":10605},{"textAlign":139},[10606],{"text":10607,"type":75,"marks":10608},"Security should live inside the system already running the gate.",[10609],{"type":149,"attrs":10610},{"color":1233},{"type":69,"attrs":10612,"content":10613},{"level":138,"textAlign":139},[10614],{"text":10615,"type":75,"marks":10616},"Convergence",[10617],{"type":149,"attrs":10618},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":10620,"content":10621},{"textAlign":139},[10622],{"text":10623,"type":75,"marks":10624},"Convergence matters because disconnected tools produce alerts, and unified systems produce decisions. A carrier-risk flag in one inbox, an ID scan in another, and a camera feed in a third are three pieces of information someone might later assemble into a conclusion, usually after the truck is already gone. That is retroactive security. It documents how the goods were lost.",[10625],{"type":149,"attrs":10626},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":10628,"content":10629},{"textAlign":139},[10630],{"text":10631,"type":75,"marks":10632},"A fraudulent carrier at the gate is a decision that has to be made before the arm lifts. It can only be made if the carrier check, the driver's identity, the appointment, and the camera feed are all the same conversation, in the same place, at the same time. That is the entire point of bringing these capabilities together. Convergence isn't about owning fewer vendors, though you will. It's about turning a pile of after-the-fact records into a decision made at the only moment a decision still matters.",[10633],{"type":149,"attrs":10634},{"color":1233},{"type":69,"attrs":10636,"content":10637},{"level":138,"textAlign":139},[10638],{"text":10639,"type":75,"marks":10640},"The yard has always been the supply chain’s soft spot",[10641],{"type":149,"attrs":10642},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":10644,"content":10645},{"textAlign":139},[10646],{"text":10647,"type":75,"marks":10648},"To be clear, there’s always been freight fraud and the yard was always the soft spot. It’s because it’s where custody is most exposed. What's new is that the excuse is gone and the stakes are higher. Solutions exist that will allow, for the first time, the facility that released the load to prove who took it, prove they were authorized to, and prove that what was left matched what was supposed to. ",[10649],{"type":149,"attrs":10650},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":10652,"content":10653},{"textAlign":139},[10654],{"text":10655,"type":75,"marks":10656},"That is what this moment in technology actually offers logistics. To give the yard the same visibility and accountability the rest of the supply chain has taken for granted for years.",[10657],{"type":149,"attrs":10658},{"color":1233},{"id":18,"url":18,"linktype":19,"fieldtype":20,"cached_url":18},[10661],"4970a15a-a518-4e01-a0de-cb3b272e0fe4","Cargo fraud has made the yard the supply chain's most exposed point, yet yard security and yard management have always been treated as separate problems bought from separate vendors. Terminal's argument: AI-native development has collapsed that tradeoff, making it possible for the first time to converge both into one system at the gate, where custody actually changes and the decision to lift the arm still matters",{"id":139,"alt":139,"name":18,"focus":139,"title":139,"source":139,"filename":18,"copyright":139,"fieldtype":1105,"meta_data":10664},{},"Why Yard Security Belongs Inside Your Yard Management System",{"id":10667,"alt":18,"name":18,"focus":18,"title":18,"source":18,"filename":10668,"copyright":18,"fieldtype":1105,"meta_data":10669,"is_external_url":49},188621303706158,"/storyblok/f/337048/800x533/789821de04/yard-gate.jpg",{},[],"Freight fraud made the yard the supply chain's soft spot. See why AI-native systems can finally converge yard security and management at the gate, where it counts.",{"value":2818,"plugin":2819},"if-trust-in-freight-is-dead-why-is-it-still-running-the-yard-","all-resources/if-trust-in-freight-is-dead-why-is-it-still-running-the-yard-",-2310,[4660,10677,2825,10678,10679],"chain of custody","security","yms","3f685df9-91c4-4a64-9531-e80ac5078855","2026-06-17T23:36:58.081Z",[],{"name":10684,"created_at":10685,"published_at":10686,"updated_at":10687,"id":10688,"uuid":10689,"content":10690,"slug":11740,"full_slug":11741,"sort_by_date":139,"position":11742,"tag_list":11743,"is_startpage":49,"parent_id":2828,"meta_data":139,"group_id":11744,"first_published_at":11745,"release_id":139,"lang":1161,"path":139,"alternates":11746,"default_full_slug":139,"translated_slugs":139},"From Paper Logs to Platforms: Why Yard Management Software Is the Missing Link in Logistics","2025-11-09T08:32:00.035Z","2026-03-27T17:34:36.602Z","2026-03-27T17:34:36.625Z",110540882098872,"9570ee4f-cca6-453d-b8a4-159c3fc44b90",{"_uid":10691,"body":10692,"link":11727,"title":10684,"author":11728,"excerpt":11729,"category":2808,"is_gated":49,"subtitle":18,"component":2809,"seo_image":11730,"seo_title":11732,"button_text":132,"cover_image":11733,"gated_asset":11737,"seo_noindex":49,"seo_description":11738,"background_color":11739,"featured_in_latest_news":49},"b743a955-ed8f-4371-8b84-f2d8b4e2e881",{"type":66,"content":10693},[10694,10702,10711,10719,10728,10742,10750,10759,10767,10775,10789,10831,10839,10848,10856,10865,10873,10939,10948,10956,10965,10973,11015,11023,11032,11040,11049,11057,11066,11074,11083,11091,11100,11108,11127,11146,11155,11174,11183,11208,11217,11225,11234,11242,11261,11275,11294,11303,11322,11331,11349,11358,11387,11396,11404,11412,11426,11458,11466,11475,11489,11498,11512,11521,11540,11549,11557,11566,11574,11583,11601,11611,11661,11670,11678,11686,11705,11719],{"type":112,"attrs":10695,"content":10696},{"textAlign":139},[10697],{"text":10698,"type":75,"marks":10699},"Walk into any logistics yard still running on paper logs, and you'll witness a familiar scene: clipboards clutched by harried staff, illegible handwriting causing confusion, and drivers waiting endlessly while someone hunts down trailer locations in a filing cabinet. These paper-based systems that once sufficed for simpler operations now buckle under modern supply chain demands.",[10700],{"type":149,"attrs":10701},{"color":1233},{"type":69,"attrs":10703,"content":10704},{"level":138,"textAlign":139},[10705],{"text":10706,"type":75,"marks":10707},"The Complexity of Today's Logistics Yards",[10708,10710],{"type":149,"attrs":10709},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":10712,"content":10713},{"textAlign":139},[10714],{"text":10715,"type":75,"marks":10716},"Today's logistics yards face unprecedented complexity. You're managing higher volumes, coordinating multiple carriers, tracking diverse asset types, and meeting tighter delivery windows—all while maintaining compliance and safety standards. The gap between what paper logs can deliver and what your operations require grows wider each day.",[10717],{"type":149,"attrs":10718},{"color":1233},{"type":69,"attrs":10720,"content":10721},{"level":138,"textAlign":139},[10722],{"text":10723,"type":75,"marks":10724},"The Solution: Yard Management Software",[10725,10727],{"type":149,"attrs":10726},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":10729,"content":10730},{"textAlign":139},[10731,10737],{"text":10732,"type":75,"marks":10733},"Yard management software",[10734,10736],{"type":149,"attrs":10735},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":10738,"type":75,"marks":10739}," represents the digital transformation your logistics operation needs. This technology bridges critical operational and data gaps that paper systems leave wide open, transforming chaotic yards into orchestrated hubs of efficiency.",[10740],{"type":149,"attrs":10741},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":10743,"content":10744},{"textAlign":139},[10745],{"text":10746,"type":75,"marks":10747},"The shift from paper logs to platforms isn't just an upgrade—it's the missing link connecting your yard operations to the speed and visibility modern logistics demands.",[10748],{"type":149,"attrs":10749},{"color":1233},{"type":69,"attrs":10751,"content":10752},{"level":138,"textAlign":139},[10753],{"text":10754,"type":75,"marks":10755},"The Limitations of Traditional Paper-Based Yard Management",[10756,10758],{"type":149,"attrs":10757},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":10760,"content":10761},{"textAlign":139},[10762],{"text":10763,"type":75,"marks":10764},"Paper logs create a chain reaction of operational bottlenecks that worsen throughout the day. When drivers arrive at your gate, they hand over paperwork that must be manually entered into systems—a process prone to human error. Misread handwriting, transposed numbers, and missing information plague these manual processes, forcing staff to chase down corrections while trucks idle at the gate.",[10765],{"type":149,"attrs":10766},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":10768,"content":10769},{"textAlign":139},[10770],{"text":10771,"type":75,"marks":10772},"The chaos intensifies as these paper records pile up. You end up with filing cabinets full of documents that offer zero visibility into current yard conditions. Where's that specific trailer? When did it arrive? What's its current status? These simple questions require physical searches through stacks of clipboards or navigating oversized spreadsheets that crash when they exceed capacity.",[10773],{"type":149,"attrs":10774},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":10776,"content":10777},{"textAlign":139},[10778,10784],{"text":10779,"type":75,"marks":10780},"Real-time visibility becomes impossible",[10781,10783],{"type":149,"attrs":10782},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":10785,"type":75,"marks":10786}," with paper-based systems. Your yard supervisor can't see which dock doors are occupied, which trailers are ready for loading, or where bottlenecks are forming. This lack of information creates:",[10787],{"type":149,"attrs":10788},{"color":1233},{"type":1404,"content":10790},[10791,10801,10811,10821],{"type":1407,"content":10792},[10793],{"type":112,"attrs":10794,"content":10795},{"textAlign":139},[10796],{"text":10797,"type":75,"marks":10798},"Extended driver wait times as staff manually locate assets",[10799],{"type":149,"attrs":10800},{"color":1233},{"type":1407,"content":10802},[10803],{"type":112,"attrs":10804,"content":10805},{"textAlign":139},[10806],{"text":10807,"type":75,"marks":10808},"Missed appointment windows due to delayed status updates",[10809],{"type":149,"attrs":10810},{"color":1233},{"type":1407,"content":10812},[10813],{"type":112,"attrs":10814,"content":10815},{"textAlign":139},[10816],{"text":10817,"type":75,"marks":10818},"Inefficient space utilization from poor asset tracking",[10819],{"type":149,"attrs":10820},{"color":1233},{"type":1407,"content":10822},[10823],{"type":112,"attrs":10824,"content":10825},{"textAlign":139},[10826],{"text":10827,"type":75,"marks":10828},"Increased detention fees from coordination failures",[10829],{"type":149,"attrs":10830},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":10832,"content":10833},{"textAlign":139},[10834],{"text":10835,"type":75,"marks":10836},"Vehicle coordination suffers dramatically under these inefficiencies in logistics. Your yard jockeys waste hours searching for specific trailers because the paper log shows a location that's three moves outdated. Inventory tracking becomes guesswork rather than data-driven decision-making, directly impacting yard throughput and your bottom line.",[10837],{"type":149,"attrs":10838},{"color":1233},{"type":69,"attrs":10840,"content":10841},{"level":138,"textAlign":139},[10842],{"text":10843,"type":75,"marks":10844},"What is Yard Management Software (YMS)?",[10845,10847],{"type":149,"attrs":10846},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":10849,"content":10850},{"textAlign":139},[10851],{"text":10852,"type":75,"marks":10853},"Yard management software is a digital tool designed to manage all activities, transactions, and assets in your logistics yard. It replaces manual methods like clipboards and spreadsheets with an automated system that tracks trailers, containers, and vehicles in real-time while coordinating the complex movements of arrivals, departures, and internal operations. ",[10854],{"type":149,"attrs":10855},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":10857,"content":10858},{"textAlign":139},[10859],{"text":10860,"type":75,"marks":10861},"Key Features of Yard Management Software",[10862,10864],{"type":149,"attrs":10863},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":10866,"content":10867},{"textAlign":139},[10868],{"text":10869,"type":75,"marks":10870},"The main functions of digital yard operations include:",[10871],{"type":149,"attrs":10872},{"color":1233},{"type":1404,"content":10874},[10875,10891,10907,10923],{"type":1407,"content":10876},[10877],{"type":112,"attrs":10878,"content":10879},{"textAlign":139},[10880,10886],{"text":10881,"type":75,"marks":10882},"Vehicle tracking",[10883,10885],{"type":149,"attrs":10884},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":10887,"type":75,"marks":10888},": Knowing the exact location of assets without needing manual scans or GPS devices.",[10889],{"type":149,"attrs":10890},{"color":1233},{"type":1407,"content":10892},[10893],{"type":112,"attrs":10894,"content":10895},{"textAlign":139},[10896,10902],{"text":10897,"type":75,"marks":10898},"Dock-slot scheduling",[10899,10901],{"type":149,"attrs":10900},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":10903,"type":75,"marks":10904},": Smartly assigning trailers to specific doors based on importance, load type, and operational limitations.",[10905],{"type":149,"attrs":10906},{"color":1233},{"type":1407,"content":10908},[10909],{"type":112,"attrs":10910,"content":10911},{"textAlign":139},[10912,10918],{"text":10913,"type":75,"marks":10914},"Check-in/check-out automation",[10915,10917],{"type":149,"attrs":10916},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":10919,"type":75,"marks":10920},": Speeding up the process of drivers entering and leaving the yard from 15-30 minutes to just a few minutes.",[10921],{"type":149,"attrs":10922},{"color":1233},{"type":1407,"content":10924},[10925],{"type":112,"attrs":10926,"content":10927},{"textAlign":139},[10928,10934],{"text":10929,"type":75,"marks":10930},"Asset inventory management",[10931,10933],{"type":149,"attrs":10932},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":10935,"type":75,"marks":10936},": Keeping track of what's in your yard, where it's located, and its current condition at all times.",[10937],{"type":149,"attrs":10938},{"color":1233},{"type":69,"attrs":10940,"content":10941},{"level":1327,"textAlign":139},[10942],{"text":10943,"type":75,"marks":10944},"Benefits of Yard Management Software",[10945,10947],{"type":149,"attrs":10946},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":10949,"content":10950},{"textAlign":139},[10951],{"text":10952,"type":75,"marks":10953},"The change happens through centralized control. With YMS, you have a single source of truth for all yard activities, eliminating information gaps that come with paper-based systems. Everyone involved—from gate guards to yard drivers to dock supervisors—can access the same real-time data, creating transparency that was impossible with manual logs.",[10954],{"type":149,"attrs":10955},{"color":1233},{"type":69,"attrs":10957,"content":10958},{"level":8636,"textAlign":139},[10959],{"text":10960,"type":75,"marks":10961},"How YMS Improves Logistics Efficiency",[10962,10964],{"type":149,"attrs":10963},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":10966,"content":10967},{"textAlign":139},[10968],{"text":10969,"type":75,"marks":10970},"Yard Management Software (YMS) brings automation to logistics by allowing customizable workflows to trigger actions automatically. For example:",[10971],{"type":149,"attrs":10972},{"color":1233},{"type":1404,"content":10974},[10975,10985,10995,11005],{"type":1407,"content":10976},[10977],{"type":112,"attrs":10978,"content":10979},{"textAlign":139},[10980],{"text":10981,"type":75,"marks":10982},"When a trailer checks in",[10983],{"type":149,"attrs":10984},{"color":1233},{"type":1407,"content":10986},[10987],{"type":112,"attrs":10988,"content":10989},{"textAlign":139},[10990],{"text":10991,"type":75,"marks":10992},"The system assigns it a parking spot",[10993],{"type":149,"attrs":10994},{"color":1233},{"type":1407,"content":10996},[10997],{"type":112,"attrs":10998,"content":10999},{"textAlign":139},[11000],{"text":11001,"type":75,"marks":11002},"Notifies the relevant team",[11003],{"type":149,"attrs":11004},{"color":1233},{"type":1407,"content":11006},[11007],{"type":112,"attrs":11008,"content":11009},{"textAlign":139},[11010],{"text":11011,"type":75,"marks":11012},"Queuing it for unloading",[11013],{"type":149,"attrs":11014},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":11016,"content":11017},{"textAlign":139},[11018],{"text":11019,"type":75,"marks":11020},"All these actions happen without any phone calls or radio dispatches involved.",[11021],{"type":149,"attrs":11022},{"color":1233},{"type":69,"attrs":11024,"content":11025},{"level":138,"textAlign":139},[11026],{"text":11027,"type":75,"marks":11028},"Key Benefits of Moving from Paper Logs to Digital Platforms",[11029,11031],{"type":149,"attrs":11030},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":11033,"content":11034},{"textAlign":139},[11035],{"text":11036,"type":75,"marks":11037},"Switching from paper-based systems to yard management software brings significant improvements to every part of yard operations. Here are some key benefits:",[11038],{"type":149,"attrs":11039},{"color":1233},{"type":69,"attrs":11041,"content":11042},{"level":1327,"textAlign":139},[11043],{"text":11044,"type":75,"marks":11045},"1. Increased Operational Efficiency",[11046,11048],{"type":149,"attrs":11047},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":11050,"content":11051},{"textAlign":139},[11052],{"text":11053,"type":75,"marks":11054},"Digital platforms eliminate the bottlenecks inherent in manual processes, leading to significant gains in operational efficiency. With automated check-in workflows and real-time asset tracking, wait times are reduced as vehicle movement through the yard is streamlined. Industry data shows productivity improvements of up to 30% when companies replace paper logs with intelligent YMS platforms.",[11055],{"type":149,"attrs":11056},{"color":1233},{"type":69,"attrs":11058,"content":11059},{"level":1327,"textAlign":139},[11060],{"text":11061,"type":75,"marks":11062},"2. Enhanced Real-Time Visibility",[11063,11065],{"type":149,"attrs":11064},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":11067,"content":11068},{"textAlign":139},[11069],{"text":11070,"type":75,"marks":11071},"Real-time visibility transforms how you manage yard activities. Instead of relying on outdated spreadsheets or radio communications, you gain instant access to accurate data about every asset, vehicle, and movement happening across your facility. This transparency extends to compliance documentation, making audits straightforward and reducing regulatory risk.",[11072],{"type":149,"attrs":11073},{"color":1233},{"type":69,"attrs":11075,"content":11076},{"level":1327,"textAlign":139},[11077],{"text":11078,"type":75,"marks":11079},"3. Improved Security Measures",[11080,11082],{"type":149,"attrs":11081},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":11084,"content":11085},{"textAlign":139},[11086],{"text":11087,"type":75,"marks":11088},"Security enhancements become systematic rather than reactive with modern YMS platforms. Access control mechanisms are incorporated to automatically verify driver credentials, track employee identification at entry points, and flag unauthorized vehicles before they enter your premises. Risk mitigation strategies are implemented that protect both your assets and your workforce.",[11089],{"type":149,"attrs":11090},{"color":1233},{"type":69,"attrs":11092,"content":11093},{"level":1327,"textAlign":139},[11094],{"text":11095,"type":75,"marks":11096},"4. Significant Cost Savings",[11097,11099],{"type":149,"attrs":11098},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":11101,"content":11102},{"textAlign":139},[11103],{"text":11104,"type":75,"marks":11105},"The financial impact of moving to digital platforms is substantial. Cost savings accumulate through multiple channels: reduced detention fees as drivers spend less time waiting, lower labor costs from automated gate processes, and decreased errors that previously resulted in misplaced inventory or scheduling conflicts. Workforce inefficiencies that drain resources when staff members spend hours searching for trailers or manually reconciling paperwork discrepancies are eliminated.",[11106],{"type":149,"attrs":11107},{"color":1233},{"type":69,"attrs":11109,"content":11110},{"level":138,"textAlign":139},[11111,11117,11121],{"text":11112,"type":75,"marks":11113},"Terminal ",[11114,11116],{"type":149,"attrs":11115},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":7427,"type":75,"marks":11118},[11119],{"type":149,"attrs":11120},{"color":1233},{"text":11122,"type":75,"marks":11123}," Approach: Reinventing Yard Logistics with AI-Native Technology",[11124,11126],{"type":149,"attrs":11125},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":11128,"content":11129},{"textAlign":139},[11130,11135,11141],{"text":11131,"type":75,"marks":11132},"Terminal Industries is leading the way in logistics innovation, specifically targeting the operational and data issues that traditional yard management faces. The company's ",[11133],{"type":149,"attrs":11134},{"color":1233},{"text":11136,"type":75,"marks":11137},"Terminal Yard Operating System™",[11138,11140],{"type":149,"attrs":11139},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":11142,"type":75,"marks":11143}," represents a fundamental shift from legacy approaches, delivering an AI-native YMS built from the ground up for modern supply chain demands.",[11144],{"type":149,"attrs":11145},{"color":1233},{"type":69,"attrs":11147,"content":11148},{"level":1327,"textAlign":139},[11149],{"text":11150,"type":75,"marks":11151},"Combining Technologies for Effective Yard Management",[11152,11154],{"type":149,"attrs":11153},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":11156,"content":11157},{"textAlign":139},[11158,11163,11169],{"text":11159,"type":75,"marks":11160},"The system's architecture combines proprietary computer vision in logistics with real-time data infrastructure and modular software applications. At the heart of this technology sits ",[11161],{"type":149,"attrs":11162},{"color":1233},{"text":11164,"type":75,"marks":11165},"Terminal-in-a-Camera™",[11166,11168],{"type":149,"attrs":11167},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":11170,"type":75,"marks":11171}," hardware, which deploys in hours without trenching or extensive infrastructure modifications. This AI-powered computer vision achieves 99.5% data accuracy in asset identification and tracking, eliminating the guesswork inherent in manual processes.",[11172],{"type":149,"attrs":11173},{"color":1233},{"type":69,"attrs":11175,"content":11176},{"level":1327,"textAlign":139},[11177],{"text":11178,"type":75,"marks":11179},"Automating Processes and Improving Efficiency",[11180,11182],{"type":149,"attrs":11181},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":11184,"content":11185},{"textAlign":139},[11186,11192,11197,11203],{"text":11187,"type":75,"marks":11188},"SmartYard™",[11189,11191],{"type":149,"attrs":11190},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":11193,"type":75,"marks":11194}," workflows leverage this visual intelligence to automate gate processes and orchestrate yard activities with precision. The results speak directly to operational impact: facilities implementing Terminal's solution report ",[11195],{"type":149,"attrs":11196},{"color":1233},{"text":11198,"type":75,"marks":11199},"50%+ throughput improvement",[11200,11202],{"type":149,"attrs":11201},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":11204,"type":75,"marks":11205}," alongside dramatic reductions in processing time and human error.",[11206],{"type":149,"attrs":11207},{"color":1233},{"type":69,"attrs":11209,"content":11210},{"level":1327,"textAlign":139},[11211],{"text":11212,"type":75,"marks":11213},"Centralized Control for Distributed Operations",[11214,11216],{"type":149,"attrs":11215},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":11218,"content":11219},{"textAlign":139},[11220],{"text":11221,"type":75,"marks":11222},"The platform's yard network capability extends these benefits across multiple facilities, providing unified visibility through a single-pane-of-glass interface. You gain centralized control over distributed operations, enabling consistent processes and data-driven decision-making regardless of geographic spread. This scalability proves particularly valuable for mid-market and large enterprise operators managing five or more warehouses, where standardization and network-wide optimization create compounding efficiency gains.",[11223],{"type":149,"attrs":11224},{"color":1233},{"type":69,"attrs":11226,"content":11227},{"level":138,"textAlign":139},[11228],{"text":11229,"type":75,"marks":11230},"Integration Capabilities for Seamless Supply Chain Operations",[11231,11233],{"type":149,"attrs":11232},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":11235,"content":11236},{"textAlign":139},[11237],{"text":11238,"type":75,"marks":11239},"Your yard doesn't operate in isolation. Modern yard management software needs to connect with the broader technology ecosystem you've already invested in. ERP Integration ensures financial data, purchase orders, and inventory records flow seamlessly between your yard and enterprise systems. TMS compatibility allows real-time coordination between transportation planning and yard execution, eliminating the communication gaps that create bottlenecks.",[11240],{"type":149,"attrs":11241},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":11243,"content":11244},{"textAlign":139},[11245,11250,11256],{"text":11246,"type":75,"marks":11247},"Terminal's Yard Operating System™ delivers ",[11248],{"type":149,"attrs":11249},{"color":1233},{"text":11251,"type":75,"marks":11252},"seamless integration with existing systems",[11253,11255],{"type":149,"attrs":11254},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":11257,"type":75,"marks":11258}," without requiring massive IT overhauls. The platform connects with your warehouse management systems (WMS), enterprise resource planning (ERP), and transportation management systems (TMS) through bi-directional data exchange. This means appointment data, shipment information, and inventory updates sync automatically across your entire operation.",[11259],{"type":149,"attrs":11260},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":11262,"content":11263},{"textAlign":139},[11264,11270],{"text":11265,"type":75,"marks":11266},"IoT sensors in yards ",[11267,11269],{"type":149,"attrs":11268},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":11271,"type":75,"marks":11272},"take visibility to another level. While GPS tracking provides location data for mobile assets, Terminal's computer vision technology eliminates the need for expensive GPS devices on every trailer. The Terminal-in-a-Camera™ hardware creates a live, camera-driven map of your entire yard, automatically tracking asset locations without manual scans or third-party devices.",[11273],{"type":149,"attrs":11274},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":11276,"content":11277},{"textAlign":139},[11278,11283,11289],{"text":11279,"type":75,"marks":11280},"The result? ",[11281],{"type":149,"attrs":11282},{"color":1233},{"text":11284,"type":75,"marks":11285},"End-to-end digital workflows",[11286,11288],{"type":149,"attrs":11287},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":11290,"type":75,"marks":11291}," that connect every touchpoint from gate arrival to dock departure. When a driver checks in, the system validates their credentials, confirms their appointment, assigns the optimal parking location, and notifies the dock team—all without a single phone call or paper form changing hands.",[11292],{"type":149,"attrs":11293},{"color":1233},{"type":69,"attrs":11295,"content":11296},{"level":138,"textAlign":139},[11297],{"text":11298,"type":75,"marks":11299},"Overcoming Common Challenges in Yard Management Through Technology",[11300,11302],{"type":149,"attrs":11301},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":11304,"content":11305},{"textAlign":139},[11306,11311,11317],{"text":11307,"type":75,"marks":11308},"The shift from paper logs to platforms directly addresses the most persistent pain points in yard operations. Advanced AI and computer vision functionalities transform how you locate and manage assets across your facility. When you're dealing with hundreds of trailers spread across multiple zones, ",[11309],{"type":149,"attrs":11310},{"color":1233},{"text":11312,"type":75,"marks":11313},"asset search reduction",[11314,11316],{"type":149,"attrs":11315},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":11318,"type":75,"marks":11319}," becomes critical to operational efficiency.",[11320],{"type":149,"attrs":11321},{"color":1233},{"type":69,"attrs":11323,"content":11324},{"level":1327,"textAlign":139},[11325],{"text":11326,"type":75,"marks":11327},"Transforming Yard Management with Terminal's Advanced Yard Application",[11328,11330],{"type":149,"attrs":11329},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":11332,"content":11333},{"textAlign":139},[11334,11339,11344],{"text":11335,"type":75,"marks":11336},"Terminal's Advanced Yard application demonstrates this transformation in action. The AI/CV-powered system delivers a ",[11337],{"type":149,"attrs":11338},{"color":1233},{"text":10286,"type":75,"marks":11340},[11341,11343],{"type":149,"attrs":11342},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":11345,"type":75,"marks":11346},", eliminating the frustrating hours spent hunting down specific trailers in sprawling yards. You no longer need yard jockeys driving around with clipboards or relying on outdated spreadsheet locations.",[11347],{"type":149,"attrs":11348},{"color":1233},{"type":69,"attrs":11350,"content":11351},{"level":1327,"textAlign":139},[11352],{"text":11353,"type":75,"marks":11354},"Cost Savings Beyond Operational Efficiency",[11355,11357],{"type":149,"attrs":11356},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":11359,"content":11360},{"textAlign":139},[11361,11366,11372,11377,11382],{"text":11362,"type":75,"marks":11363},"The financial impact extends beyond operational efficiency. ",[11364],{"type":149,"attrs":11365},{"color":1233},{"text":11367,"type":75,"marks":11368},"Driver detention fees reduction",[11369,11371],{"type":149,"attrs":11370},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":11373,"type":75,"marks":11374}," represents a significant cost-saving opportunity that paper-based systems simply cannot address. Terminal's technology achieves a ",[11375],{"type":149,"attrs":11376},{"color":1233},{"text":2537,"type":75,"marks":11378},[11379,11381],{"type":149,"attrs":11380},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":11383,"type":75,"marks":11384}," by accelerating gate processes and ensuring trailers are precisely located when drivers arrive. This reduction is not just a figure; it reflects a profound shift towards more efficient operations. You're cutting costs while improving driver satisfaction and carrier relationships—a dual benefit that directly impacts your bottom line and operational reputation.",[11385],{"type":149,"attrs":11386},{"color":1233},{"type":69,"attrs":11388,"content":11389},{"level":138,"textAlign":139},[11390],{"text":11391,"type":75,"marks":11392},"Future Trends Shaping Yard Management Software",[11393,11395],{"type":149,"attrs":11394},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":11397,"content":11398},{"textAlign":139},[11399],{"text":11400,"type":75,"marks":11401},"The yard management landscape is experiencing rapid technological evolution that extends far beyond current capabilities.",[11402],{"type":149,"attrs":11403},{"color":1233},{"type":69,"attrs":11405,"content":11406},{"level":1327,"textAlign":139},[11407],{"text":8305,"type":75,"marks":11408},[11409,11411],{"type":149,"attrs":11410},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":11413,"content":11414},{"textAlign":139},[11415,11421],{"text":11416,"type":75,"marks":11417},"AI predictive analytics",[11418,11420],{"type":149,"attrs":11419},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":11422,"type":75,"marks":11423}," are transforming how facilities anticipate and respond to operational demands. You'll see systems that:",[11424],{"type":149,"attrs":11425},{"color":1233},{"type":1404,"content":11427},[11428,11438,11448],{"type":1407,"content":11429},[11430],{"type":112,"attrs":11431,"content":11432},{"textAlign":139},[11433],{"text":11434,"type":75,"marks":11435},"Forecast trailer arrival patterns",[11436],{"type":149,"attrs":11437},{"color":1233},{"type":1407,"content":11439},[11440],{"type":112,"attrs":11441,"content":11442},{"textAlign":139},[11443],{"text":11444,"type":75,"marks":11445},"Predict equipment maintenance needs before failures occur",[11446],{"type":149,"attrs":11447},{"color":1233},{"type":1407,"content":11449},[11450],{"type":112,"attrs":11451,"content":11452},{"textAlign":139},[11453],{"text":11454,"type":75,"marks":11455},"Optimize dock scheduling based on historical patterns and real-time conditions",[11456],{"type":149,"attrs":11457},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":11459,"content":11460},{"textAlign":139},[11461],{"text":11462,"type":75,"marks":11463},"These predictive insights allow you to shift from reactive problem-solving to proactive yard orchestration.",[11464],{"type":149,"attrs":11465},{"color":1233},{"type":69,"attrs":11467,"content":11468},{"level":1327,"textAlign":139},[11469],{"text":11470,"type":75,"marks":11471},"2. Blockchain for Enhanced Accountability",[11472,11474],{"type":149,"attrs":11473},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":11476,"content":11477},{"textAlign":139},[11478,11484],{"text":11479,"type":75,"marks":11480},"Blockchain logistics applications",[11481,11483],{"type":149,"attrs":11482},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":11485,"type":75,"marks":11486}," are emerging as powerful tools for creating tamper-proof audit trails within yard operations. You can leverage distributed ledger technology to establish immutable records of every asset movement, gate transaction, and custody transfer. This creates unprecedented accountability across your supply chain partners and simplifies compliance verification during audits. Smart contracts built on blockchain can automatically trigger payments when specific yard milestones are met, reducing disputes and accelerating cash flow.",[11487],{"type":149,"attrs":11488},{"color":1233},{"type":69,"attrs":11490,"content":11491},{"level":1327,"textAlign":139},[11492],{"text":11493,"type":75,"marks":11494},"3. IoT Sensors for Real-Time Monitoring",[11495,11497],{"type":149,"attrs":11496},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":11499,"content":11500},{"textAlign":139},[11501,11507],{"text":11502,"type":75,"marks":11503},"IoT sensor advancements",[11504,11506],{"type":149,"attrs":11505},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":11508,"type":75,"marks":11509}," are enabling granular monitoring capabilities you couldn't achieve with traditional methods. Modern sensors track trailer temperature for cold chain compliance, monitor tire pressure on yard equipment, and detect unauthorized door openings in real-time. You're able to receive instant alerts when assets deviate from expected conditions, allowing immediate intervention before minor issues escalate into costly problems. The convergence of IoT data with AI-powered analytics creates a self-learning yard ecosystem that continuously refines its operational efficiency.",[11510],{"type":149,"attrs":11511},{"color":1233},{"type":69,"attrs":11513,"content":11514},{"level":138,"textAlign":139},[11515],{"text":11516,"type":75,"marks":11517},"Why Yard Management Software is the Missing Link in Modern Logistics",[11518,11520],{"type":149,"attrs":11519},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":11522,"content":11523},{"textAlign":139},[11524,11529,11535],{"text":11525,"type":75,"marks":11526},"The gap between warehouse management systems and transportation management systems creates a visibility black hole where trailers disappear into yards, drivers wait without updates, and operations teams scramble with outdated information. ",[11527],{"type":149,"attrs":11528},{"color":1233},{"text":11530,"type":75,"marks":11531},"Supply chain optimization",[11532,11534],{"type":149,"attrs":11533},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":11536,"type":75,"marks":11537}," requires complete transparency at every point, yet traditional paper-based methods leave yards operating in the dark ages while the rest of logistics modernizes.",[11538],{"type":149,"attrs":11539},{"color":1233},{"type":69,"attrs":11541,"content":11542},{"level":1327,"textAlign":139},[11543],{"text":11544,"type":75,"marks":11545},"The Complexity of Managing Logistics",[11546,11548],{"type":149,"attrs":11547},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":11550,"content":11551},{"textAlign":139},[11552],{"text":11553,"type":75,"marks":11554},"You're managing a complex orchestration of assets, drivers, dock doors, and shipments that requires split-second coordination. Paper logs can't provide the real-time information you need to make informed decisions when a driver arrives early, a shipment priority changes, or dock capacity shifts unexpectedly.",[11555],{"type":149,"attrs":11556},{"color":1233},{"type":69,"attrs":11558,"content":11559},{"level":1327,"textAlign":139},[11560],{"text":11561,"type":75,"marks":11562},"How YMS Platforms Help",[11563,11565],{"type":149,"attrs":11564},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":11567,"content":11568},{"textAlign":139},[11569],{"text":11570,"type":75,"marks":11571},"YMS platforms fill this critical gap by changing yards from chaotic holding areas into strategically managed hubs where every asset location, every move, and every delay becomes actionable data.",[11572],{"type":149,"attrs":11573},{"color":1233},{"type":69,"attrs":11575,"content":11576},{"level":8636,"textAlign":139},[11577],{"text":11578,"type":75,"marks":11579},"The Benefits of Digital Transformation",[11580,11582],{"type":149,"attrs":11581},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":11584,"content":11585},{"textAlign":139},[11586,11590,11596],{"text":3884,"type":75,"marks":11587},[11588],{"type":149,"attrs":11589},{"color":1233},{"text":11591,"type":75,"marks":11592},"digital transformation benefits",[11593,11595],{"type":149,"attrs":11594},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":11597,"type":75,"marks":11598}," go beyond operational efficiency. You gain the flexibility to adapt when disruptions occur—whether that's unexpected volume spikes, weather delays, or equipment shortages.",[11599],{"type":149,"attrs":11600},{"color":1233},{"type":69,"attrs":11602,"content":11604},{"level":11603,"textAlign":139},5,[11605],{"text":11606,"type":75,"marks":11607},"Key Areas of Improvement with YMS",[11608,11610],{"type":149,"attrs":11609},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"type":1404,"content":11612},[11613,11629,11645],{"type":1407,"content":11614},[11615],{"type":112,"attrs":11616,"content":11617},{"textAlign":139},[11618,11624],{"text":11619,"type":75,"marks":11620},"Instant Visibility:",[11621,11623],{"type":149,"attrs":11622},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":11625,"type":75,"marks":11626}," YMS provides real-time insights into yard capacity, allowing you to proactively manage resources and avoid bottlenecks.",[11627],{"type":149,"attrs":11628},{"color":1233},{"type":1407,"content":11630},[11631],{"type":112,"attrs":11632,"content":11633},{"textAlign":139},[11634,11640],{"text":11635,"type":75,"marks":11636},"Predictive Insights:",[11637,11639],{"type":149,"attrs":11638},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":11641,"type":75,"marks":11642}," By analyzing historical data, YMS can forecast potential issues and help you plan accordingly.",[11643],{"type":149,"attrs":11644},{"color":1233},{"type":1407,"content":11646},[11647],{"type":112,"attrs":11648,"content":11649},{"textAlign":139},[11650,11656],{"text":11651,"type":75,"marks":11652},"Automated Workflows:",[11653,11655],{"type":149,"attrs":11654},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":11657,"type":75,"marks":11658}," With YMS, you can streamline processes and reduce manual intervention, resulting in faster decision-making and improved productivity.",[11659],{"type":149,"attrs":11660},{"color":1233},{"type":69,"attrs":11662,"content":11663},{"level":1327,"textAlign":139},[11664],{"text":11665,"type":75,"marks":11666},"Shifting from Reactive to Proactive Management",[11667,11669],{"type":149,"attrs":11668},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":11671,"content":11672},{"textAlign":139},[11673],{"text":11674,"type":75,"marks":11675},"Digitization empowers you to move from reactive problem-solving to proactive management. You can identify patterns in dwell times, optimize dock scheduling based on past data, and prevent detention fees before they accumulate. This knowledge creates a sustainable flow of goods that reduces wasted fuel, minimizes empty miles, supports environmental goals, and improves your financial performance.",[11676],{"type":149,"attrs":11677},{"color":1233},{"type":69,"attrs":11679,"content":11680},{"level":138,"textAlign":139},[11681],{"text":2740,"type":75,"marks":11682},[11683,11685],{"type":149,"attrs":11684},{"color":1233}